texts.text: >The day after that dreadful sound filled the air.

*Pant*
That took more effort that I was expecting...
But we finally got it. Time to finish this.
>Vince's demon puts the rampaging demon in a strong hold.

No, let go!
Release me!
I require blood! Human blood!
We're not letting you suck anyone's blood.
You're lucky that these people were left anemic and not dead,
but do you have any idea how many victims you left in your wake?
Hey, I know what those are! Smartphones, right?!
Another one?!

I'll break these too!
Take this!
Ugh, you pest...!
Let's go!
Leave it to me!
*Groan*
Dammit, what is it with these things? Why are they acting like this?
They're not usually this strong either.

*Groan*
I need... Blood...!
Huh? What was that?
I heard it... That sound... It makes me feel so restless...!

What sound...?
Wait, you mean that thing we heard yesterday?!
Which is why... I must have...!
>The demon attempts to flee!
Dammit, that little shit!
More! I must have more!
Aight, so we got a whole bunch of demons runnin' around the city...
And it's stretchin' us too thin.
Yeah, and I think I know what caused all this.
It's that horrid sound we heard yesterday.
Yes, I've been seeing that people are calling this the "sound of the end".
In other words, the apocalypse is coming.
Aight, but for now, all we can do is keep playin' whack-a-mole with these demons.
As much as I'd like to find out what this "sound of the end" is...
This sound, it's...!
>The dreadful noise returns and echoes throughout the city...!
It's that sound again...!
Yo, we gotta find out where it's comin' from!
It's coming from all over... There's no way to tell where it's source is...
Aight, time to split up and find it!
A demon's behind this shit. I'm sure of it!
Roger!
>You, Megakin and Shiori follow the sound back to a temple.
Based on how it echoed, this should be where its source is...
But it's too hard to pinpoint exactly where.
Yo, we just gotta brute force it until we figure it out...
You, humans.
Have you seen a golden horn anywhere?
Another demon?
Let's hear him out.

Newbie, hold up.
He doesn't seem hostile.
Aight, why not? I'm not sensin' any hostility here.
Indeed.
I have no quarrel with you. I am simply in search of my horn.
Yo, that's great and all... But what's this golden horn you're talkin' about?
Ain't that thing in your hand what you're lookin' for?
This is but a convincing replica.
Have you seen one just like this?
The true horn has much more pronounced sheen to it...
No, we haven't.
I don't think so.
I see... But I could have sworn that I heard my horn being sound just now...
Your horn?
Yes, the very same sound that you seem to have heard just now.

That was my horn.
The Gjallarhorn itself.
Yo, that sound came from a demon...?!
Demon? I am no such thing.
I am he who keeps watch over the Bifrost, the bridge to Asgard.
I am Heimdall, one of the Aesir.
Yo, we're sorry. We didn't mean to offend you.
And you are forgiven. I am aware that humans cannot distinguish my kind from those foul creatures.
Conversely, I see how each of your faces are full of distinctive features.
Anyway, it's my turn to ask some questions.
Demons started going wild after they heard your horn being sound.
Is that something the Gjallarhorn is supposed to do?
Ah, I see. In a way, yes.
The Gjalarhorn is meant to be sound when the giants attack Asgard,
and is to be blown by me so that I may warn the gods.
In other words, it is meant to signal the onset of Ragnarok.
Yo, so it really is "the sound of the end"...!
Indeed. I am certain that these demons felt this sound reverberate throughout their bodies.
They are compelled to fulfill their various purposes.
Some are likely doing so subconsciously.
Yo, that's why they're all actin' this way?
Luckily, only the wimpy ones are acting like this.
The greater powers that be are still observing this situation.
But because the Gjallarhorn was indeed sound,
they will ultimately have no choice but to help usher forth Ragnarok.
What happens when these "greater powers" join in?
Ah, if they decide to clash all at once, the end will come.
Asgard will fall into chaos along with Midgard, your world.

Yo, holy shit...
The world's actually gonna end.
Why is something as dangerous as this being sound in the first place?
I feel great shame in this, but it appears that Loki somehow deceived Mimir,
and managed to steal the Gjallarhorn from the Well of Wisdom.
However, I surmise that Loki lacks the courage to blow it,
which is why it having found its way here can only mean one thing.
He tricked a human into taking it and blowing it for him.
So if we trace this sound back to where it's comin' from,
we'll stop the world from endin', right...?
That is correct.
My station compels me to retrieve the Gjallarhorn as well.
>Just as he says that, the same dreadful sound echoes once more.
Yes, this is the Gjallarhorn!
It sounded close too...!
But I still couldn't tell where it was coming from...!
My ears are the sharpest in existence. This way!
There! That human is the one sounding it!
Naoto?!
Shiori...?!
Do you have any idea what you're doing?! Do you?!
You know him?
Is he a friend?
Yeah, we were in the same research group during college.
No, we were just in the same research group during college.
Return my horn to me at once.
No, that's not happening.
Then you leave me no choice...
Heimdall, give us a minute, will you?
So you are his acquaintance. Fine, but be quick about it.
I will.
It's been a while, Shiori.
I never thought that you were capable of something like this.
But to be fair, that creep, Shinonome, had some kind of affinity for you...
Did she put you up to this?

No.
I'm doing this of my own free will.
Shinonome already gave up on me. Pretty ruthlessly too.
That's why I want the world to end. This world that doesn't give a crap about me...
>Naoto prepares to blow the horn once more.
No, stop...
Why don't you hand that horn over to me?
Shinonome...!

*Chuckle*
I see that your horn there has the ability to rile up demons.
It will go beautifully with my research.
Shinonome, what do you mean...?
Demons started running around en masse after that horn was sound.
I am certain that these two events are connected.
I decided to trace the sound back to its source and found you holding it.
If you give that horn to me, Naoto, I will welcome you back into my arms.
Naoto, this bitch dumped you once already.
Don't let her trick you like this.
But... But I...
